## Part 2 — Goals

> ### PROMPT 2
>
> Add a Goals system to the tracker. Goals live in a `goals` array and render as cards with progress bars on both the Goals tab and the Dashboard. Each goal is editable inline (changes save to localStorage). Support these goal *types*, because different goals measure progress differently:
>
> - **`payoff`** — a debt to clear: `{ total, paid, monthlyTarget, targetDate }`. Progress = paid / total.
> - **`lump`** — a one-off amount due by a date: `{ total, paid, dueDate }`.
> - **`tracking`** — a balance you're chipping at: `{ currentBalance, basePayment, extraTargetMonthly }`.
> - **`annual`** — a yearly contribution target: `{ annualTargetCombined, contributedThisFY }`. Progress vs the FY target.
> - **`rate`** — a run-rate target like business revenue: `{ currentMonthlyAvg, targetAnnual }`. Progress = (monthly×12) / target.
> - **`milestone`** — a future event with a target window: `{ targetWindowStart, targetWindowEnd }`.
>
> Each goal has an `icon` (emoji), `title`, and `note`. Ask me for my actual goals and set them up.

